      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's a very honest question, and the feeling that nothing matters is a real, painful place to be. When everything feels pointless, the idea of a \"point\" becomes a massive, exhausting concept. Sometimes, the only real point is in the quiet, immediate relief of just letting the pressure drop, even if that relief is temporary. You don't have to find a grand purpose right now; just finding a moment of stillness might be enough.",
      "source": "target",
